The board shall issue a license to:
An individual who holds a valid license from another state, who meets requirements specified in KRS 327.050 and who has no imposed or pending disciplinary actions.
An individual who has been educated as a physical therapist outside the United States and who has:
Completed the application process;
Provided satisfactory evidence to the board that his or her education is substantially equivalent to the requirements for physical therapists educated in United States accredited educational programs;
Provided written proof that the school of physical therapy education outside the United States is recognized by its own ministry of education;
Successfully completed the examinations provided for in KRS 327.050;
Passed the board-approved English language proficiency examinations if English is not his or her native language;
Successfully completed, prior to licensure, a board-approved, supervised practice period of not less than three (3) months nor more than six (6) months, under the direct supervision of a physical therapist who holds an unrestricted Kentucky license. This requirement may be satisfied by at least three (3) months of supervised practice as a physical therapist in a state with license requirements comparable to or more stringent than those of Kentucky;
Provided proof of legal authorization to reside and seek employment in the United States or its territories;
Provided proof of authorization to practice as a physical therapist without limitations in the country where the professional education occurred;
Submitted to a prescreening process by an agency approved by the board; and
Submitted educational credentials to the board for evaluation by an agency approved by the board.
